  <!-- Comparison -->
  <section id="comparison" class="py-20 sm:py-28 border-t border-slate-800/50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-slate-100 mb-4">Coming from OpenClaw?</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
          OpenClaw is an incredible project &mdash; 250k+ GitHub stars, 22+ messaging channels, voice, device apps,
          5,000+ community skills, and now backed by an open-source foundation. It&rsquo;s the most popular AI agent framework for a reason.
        </p>
        <p class="text-slate-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto mt-4 leading-relaxed">
          The difference isn&rsquo;t just which model runs underneath.
          It&rsquo;s <span class="text-teal-400 font-medium">what the framework treats as fundamental.</span>
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- The core difference -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-12">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/40 p-8">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
            <div class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-slate-600"></div>
            <span class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wider">OpenClaw</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Infrastructure for <strong class="text-slate-200">capability</strong>. Gets AI into every platform &mdash;
            22+ channels, voice, device apps, 28 model providers. Identity defined in files, loaded at startup, hoped for after that.
            Memory as files on disk to search. No built-in values, drift detection, or consistency tracking.
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm">Best for: AI everywhere, multi-model, maximum reach.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-teal-500/20 bg-teal-500/5 p-8 glow-teal">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
            <div class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-teal-400 animate-pulse"></div>
            <span class="text-sm font-medium text-teal-400 uppercase tracking-wider">Instar</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-slate-200 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Infrastructure for <strong class="text-teal-300">coherence</strong>. Built on real Claude Code sessions with
            full extended thinking. Identity enforced through hooks &mdash; not just loaded, guaranteed.
            Values that evolve. Relationships with depth. Consistency tracked across sessions.
          </p>
          <p class="text-teal-400/70 text-sm">Best for: a trusted partner that knows who it is and who you are.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Coherence comparison -->
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-200 mb-6 text-center">The coherence gap</h3>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12">
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/40 p-5">
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-teal-300 mb-2">Identity that survives</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">OpenClaw loads identity files at startup &mdash; but after 8+ tool calls, personality drifts. Sub-agent hand-offs lose character. Instar <em>enforces</em> identity through hooks at every compaction and restart boundary. Structure, not hope.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/40 p-5">
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-teal-300 mb-2">Memory with meaning</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">OpenClaw stores daily logs and searches them with BM25+vector. Instar adds structured consolidation, rolling summaries, episodic memory, and unanswered message detection. Not just files to search &mdash; experiences to understand.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/40 p-5">
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-teal-300 mb-2">Values, not just personality</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">OpenClaw has SOUL.md for personality. Instar has a three-tier value hierarchy &mdash; personal, shared, and organizational &mdash; with decision journaling and drift detection. Values that evolve with experience, not static character files.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/40 p-5">
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-teal-300 mb-2">Relationships, not contacts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">OpenClaw offers CRM-style tracking &mdash; health scores, follow-up reminders. Instar tracks relational depth: themes, significance, arc summaries. The difference between knowing <em>when</em> you talked and knowing <em>what matters</em> to someone.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/40 p-5">
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-teal-300 mb-2">Consistency you can verify</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">OpenClaw has no promise tracking or contradiction detection. Instar journals decisions with reasoning, detects drift from purpose, and tracks commitments across sessions. Your agent can explain why it did what it did.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/40 p-5">
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-teal-300 mb-2">Safety from coherence</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">OpenClaw secures the <em>system</em> (Docker, sandboxing, permissions). Instar secures the <em>decisions</em> &mdash; LLM-supervised gates, adaptive trust per service, autonomy profiles that grow with the agent. Born from real incidents, not threat models.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/40 p-5">
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-teal-300 mb-2">Evolution, not just skills</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">OpenClaw agents can install community skills (5,400+). Instar agents evolve their own infrastructure &mdash; dedicated evolution agents, proposal queues, learning registries, capability gap tracking. Growth that compounds.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/40 p-5">
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-teal-300 mb-2">Full Claude Code power</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">Every session is a real Claude Code process &mdash; extended thinking, native tools, sub-agents, MCP servers, hooks, skills. Every feature Anthropic ships, your agent gets automatically. No gateway abstraction layer.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Where OpenClaw leads -->
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-800/30 p-6 mb-6">
        <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed text-center">
          <span class="text-slate-300 font-medium">Where OpenClaw leads:</span>
          22+ messaging channels, voice &amp; phone calls, device apps (macOS, Android), 28+ AI model providers, Docker sandboxing, 5,000+ community skills,
          and a massive open-source community backed by a foundation with OpenAI sponsorship.
          If breadth and ecosystem scale matter most to you, OpenClaw is remarkable.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="text-center text-slate-400 text-sm max-w-lg mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        OpenClaw gives agents amazing hands. Instar gives agents <span class="text-teal-400">a mind</span> &mdash;
        identity that persists, values that evolve, and coherence you can trust.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

